This directory contains exactly one file, `index.html`, which is the entire viz subtree — a self-contained static HTML/JS/CSS viewer with no build step, no other source files, and no subdirectories.

Since there's only one child, this rollup adds nothing `index.html.ctx` doesn't already state: it's a single-page tree browser for `../out/viz-data.json`, with a hand-maintained JS mirror of the Rust stroke-parsing logic in `crates/steno/src/stroke/keys.rs` that must be kept in lockstep, and global mutable state (`path`, `axisSelection`, `oneLinerActive`, `currentOneLinerRoot`) driving re-renders. Any change here starts and ends in that one file — there is no cross-file coupling to describe within this directory.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so there is nothing to check divergence against.